BEHAVIORAL CORRECTION (iter53, self-caught): wrote a stray printf to .gm/exec-spool/in/prd-resolve/dummy.txt with empty body {} intending a no-op, which dispatched a REAL prd-resolve verb that rejected it -> deviation.prd-resolve-unknown-id (the only deviation in an otherwise-clean window). FIX: never write throwaway/placeholder/no-op spool dispatches. Every file written to .gm/exec-spool/in/<verb>/ IS a real verb invocation the watcher services; there is no such thing as a harmless dummy spool write. If you need a no-op in a shell pipeline, use echo or : not a spool path.